(e) A 1MHz resonant tank inductor in a GaN-based converter
Q5. Temperature derating and design margin:
A ferrite core has B_sat = 0.45T at 25°C. The B_sat vs temperature characteristic is approximately linear, dropping to 0.28T at 125°C.
(a) Find the temperature coefficient of B_sat in T/°C
(b) Find B_sat at 85°C (typical maximum operating temperature for consumer electronics)
(c) A converter inductor is designed with B_peak = 0.20T at 25°C. What safety margin (as percentage of B_sat) does this give at 25°C?
(d) At 85°C operating temperature, what safety margin remains?
(e) If the safety margin at 85°C is considered insufficient (less than 20% is risky), what B_peak should you design to at 25°C to ensure at least 30% margin at 85°C?
